fields.name: Yoga
fields.description:
It’s time to roll out your yoga mat and discover the combination of physical and mental exercises that for thousands of years have hooked yoga practitioners around the globe. The beauty of yoga is that you don’t have to be a yogi or yogini to reap the benefits. Whether you are young or old, overweight or fit, yoga has the power to calm the mind and strengthen the body. Don’t be intimidated by yoga terminology, fancy yoga studios and complicated poses. Yoga is for everyone.

The mental and spiritual aspects of yoga focus on developing mindfulness. This increases your awareness on many levels.

It can make you more conscious of how different foods affect your mind, body, and spirit.

Practicing yoga can help improve the quality of your sleep. You may find that you’re able to fall asleep more easily and sleep more deeply when you have a consistent yoga practice. Ideally, you should sleep between 6 and 9 hours each night.

fields.name: Boxing
fields.description: Fitness boxing is also a great aerobic exercise. Aerobic exercise gets your heart pumping and helps lower the risk of high blood pressure, heart disease, stroke, and diabetes. It can strengthen bones and muscles, burn more calories, and lift mood.

fields.name: Weight Training
fields.description: No one hits the gym hoping for so-so results. You go in wanting to get 100% out of every rep, run and hard-earned bead of sweat. Weight training is a common type of strength training for developing the strength and size of skeletal muscles. It utilizes the force of gravity in the form of weighted bars, dumbbells or weight stacks in order to oppose the force generated by muscle through concentric or eccentric contraction.

fields.name: HIT Training
fields.description: High-intensity training (HIT) is a form of strength training popularized in the 1970s by Arthur Jones, the founder of Nautilus. ... The training focuses on performing quality weight training repetitions to the point of momentary muscular failure. The training takes into account the number of repetitions, the amount of weight, and the amount of time the muscle is exposed to tension in order to maximize the amount of muscle fiber recruitment.

fields.name: Resistance
fields.description: Resistance training are exercises that cause the muscles to contract against an external resistance with the expectation of increases in strength, tone, mass, and/or endurance. The external resistance can be dumbbells, rubber exercise tubing, your own body weight, bricks, bottles of water, or any other object that causes the muscles to contract. Resistance training is perfect for beginners who whish to eventualy move up to weight training.

fields.name: Running
fields.description: Running strength exercises. If you want to run faster or further, building strength in your legs is a vital part of improving your running. Not only do regular targeted running strength exercises help you improve your running strength, it's also great for developing speed and for injury prevention.

fields.name: Gabbi B
fields.bio:
I provide a one stop shop for all of your exercise and nutrition needs! I am an exercise physiologist, certified personal trainer, group exercise instructor, Pilates teacher and dancer as well as a Registered Dietitian. My combination of exercise and nutrition services, combined with my extensive academic background in each, will help you get the results you're looking for - whether you want to lose weight, build muscle, look more toned, get in shape, develop an exercise routine, or learn how to eat right and exercise for life.

I have a Master's in Exercise Physiology from Columbia University and designed my own major in college to study exercise science, anatomy, physiology, nutrition, kinesiology and psychology. I completed my training as a Registered Dietitian through NYU's graduate nutrition program, as I strongly believe in helping clients achieve their goals holistically through personalized nutrition in addition to exercise.

My extensive academic backgrounds in exercise, nutrition and health provides the basis for my programs. I design all of my clients' workouts based on the most up-to-date exercise science principles as well as client needs and goals. I also create an individualized meal plan for each client, provide assistance with eating behaviors, and offer constant support. I have worked with a broad spectrum of clients spanning a variety of ages, weights, and fitness levels: I have helped individuals who want to lose weight, get in shape, overcome disordered eating, reduce chronic pain , increase energy, improve health and enhance daily functioning. I have also worked with clients with various issues and injuries, including lower back pain, arthritis, poor balance, scoliosis, joint instability, cardiac disease, and diabetes. I view each client as whole person, taking into account his/her entire lifestyle and health status in order to forge the best possible path towards the client's goals.

What to Expect

A training session with me will be smartly planned, challenging, form-focused, personalized, and fun. I use sound exercise science principles to ensure that each session is properly designed with a dynamic warm up, exercise progression that meets the client's needs/ goals, and stretch/ cool down. As the session progresses, I adjust my plan based on client needs and performance. I ensure that the client executes proper form for each exercise: I want to every client to exercise safely and effectively, and also to understand the proper muscles to engage so that they move properly in their other workouts. I balance my focus on precision with a down-to-earth demeanor: I keep my training sessions friendly and enjoyable while motivating the client to work harder than he/she thought possible. I ensure the client keeps moving and feels good with a workout that blends cardio, strength and flexibility.

Specialties

  • Running
  • High Intensity
  • Calisthenics
  • Core

fields.name: John V
fields.bio:
Hello and thank you for your interest! My number one objective is to help my clients achieve their goals using the most efficient tools and methods available. I have been training people for six years and have worked with many different people from young, athletic men and women, to beginners, to people simply looking to stay or become healthy, mobile and strong, and shed a few pounds. I love working with people and helping them better themselves.

I prefer foundational movements and apply different modalities including my favorite, traditional strength training, as well as body-weight work, coordination and stability movements. I believe form is paramount to training safely and effectively. I'm currently studying to become a Physical Therapist. As a type one diabetic and celiac, I also have an extensive background in nutrition and different diets. I work in both gyms and home environments, getting creative if necessary. Whether you are looking for one session or a longer term relationship with a trainer, I hope we can work together and achieve your goals.

Message me for any information and to see if we are a good match! I work mostly in Astoria and LIC, and Manhattan. I try my best to work out the best schedules for myself and my clients.

What to Expect

Clear communication, attention to detail and on-the-go correction, and a workout that will bring them closer to their goal. I like to start with a small warmup/prep, then the prescribed set of movements.

Client Success Story

One of my favorite successes was from a young female client who went from only doing a few knee pushups to sets of 10 full pushups in only a couple of months. Many take the humble pushup for granted, but relative to her starting point, she had made great strides in upper body strength and more importantly, confidence in the gym.

Specialties

  • Aerobics
  • High Intensity
  • Calisthenics
  • Core

fields.name: Louis L
fields.bio:
My name is Louis Labonte and I’m an ISSA CPT with 9 years of professional experience in training and certified as a nutritionist.
In 2010 , before I become a fitness trainer , I was obese along with diabetes type 2 and at that time I did not take that matter serious at hands until one day I was sitting in couch and I felt my heart is pounding with a heavy breathing signs and suddenly I realized that I had a major stroke .
During that time I was 230 pound and quite be honest I thought that my life will stop at this point and I did not know what the next step to live an healthy life due to my complications.
Luckily one day , one of my friend who know about my issues was introduced me to one of the top fitness experts by name Jimstoppany.com to follow up some fitness training program via online .
Since after all my life and health got better and I starting to learn my fitness knowledge and expertise start to grow by learning different workout mechanisms, training system and goals, dieting .
When it comes to fitness know one can beat me in that categories and I do make sure that I read and study tone of article about fitness program, proper training design to implement on my self and on others .
I will apply the same methods that I learned throughout my experience in training and along working with others to provide into your training l .

My responsibility as your personal trainer is to find the right training program that fit your overall goal and also correct all the exercise form in order to prevent any type of pain and injuries .
I create custom training programs and dieting for your specific needs and goals. You will find that all of my programs focus on the whole body. There are many benefits to training the full body:

1) Build muscle mass / tone it up
2) burn calories
3) Build strength/stamina
3) Fit for your overall fitness fitness .
My commitment to you: I want you to succeed no matter what your goals are. If you want a trainer that cares, is reliable and that I am the trainer for you. Whether you are a novice in the gym or a trained veteran, my training program will help take your fitness goals to the next level .
I guarantee you will find your happiness, joy, and satisfaction.

What to Expect

My main focus is to help get the result and reach your goal. I will demonstrate you how to lift weight in a properly manner and design a work out plan for you base on your need. I will instruct you with proper nutrition plan as well. All my work is fun.

Specialties

  • Aerobics
  • High Intensity
  • Calisthenics
  • Core

fields.name: Brittany W
fields.bio:
Hi, my name is Brittany. I'm currently a personal trainer at one of New York's top fitness centers. I am NASM, Precision Nutrition level 1 and pre/post natal certified. I've always been interested in fitness. I've been a dancer my whole life, I did cross country in middle school, track in high school and started lifting in college (and never stopped). I pursued a degree in finance, but fitness has always been my passion. I started training my friends and coworkers for fun, then one day I decided that I would go full-hearted into personal training and leave my finance career.

What to Expect

My sessions last for an hour. Usually we will start with foam rolling (if you can you can do this on your own before I get there). Then we will so some dynamic warming up. Followed by 2 circuits of resistance training, each with 3 exercises for 4 sets ( depending on the goals of the client). After that we will do 10 minutes of interval cardio (depending on goal and time allotted). Followed by stretching.

Specialties

  • Aerobics
  • Bodyweight Training
  • Calisthenics
  • Core
